cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI

This paper deals with the analysis of information propagation in online social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is specifically dedicated to the study of social networks and their properties. The paper also deals with data analysis and modeling, which could place it in the cs.SD (Software Development) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical differences between endogenous and exogenous influence, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also uses network analysis techniques, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. Finally, the paper deals with the characterization of individual users and groups, which could place it in the cs.SOC (Social and Community Computing) category.
